# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# WHITELIST repo. Ignore EVERYTHING by default, then re-include only the small
# set of safe, publishable source files below. This guarantees that the API key,
# the copyrighted primary-source libraries / manifests / embeddings, the
# private portfolio records, and all local backups are NEVER committed — even
# if new files appear in this directory later. The public site deploys from
# /docs (see below); everything else stays out.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*

# Re-include only these:
!/.gitignore
!/README.md
!/requirements.txt
!/furton_server.py
!/furton_embed.py
!/furton_rechunk.py
!/furton_committee.html
!/furton_tradelog.html
!/furton_performance.html
!/furton_capture_positions.py

# The public site, served by GitHub Pages from /docs (moved off Netlify
# 2026-07-06). Contains ONLY already-public content: the site HTML, the
# published data files, and the methodology PDF. Private records (holdings/,
# weekly_records/, screens/, keys, libraries) remain ignored as before.
!/docs/
!/docs/**
